   3.86111618360636*^9, 3.8611161837967443`*^9}, {3.8611162292760353`*^9, 
   3.861116229731387*^9}, {3.861126722413526*^9, 3.861126724437828*^9}, {
   3.861279763810367*^9, 3.8612797756144953`*^9}, {3.862900036774612*^9, 
   3.862900040040677*^9}, {3.8684162535977497`*^9, 3.868416281738037*^9}, 
   3.874285491826564*^9, {3.87428558681485*^9, 3.8742856430668697`*^9}, {
   3.874285677126814*^9, 3.8742858663363*^9}, {3.874313888831748*^9, 
   3.874313899863257*^9}, {3.874313939909382*^9, 3.8743139458837223`*^9}, {
   3.8746361891426783`*^9, 3.8746361897980623`*^9}, 3.874725002844326*^9, {
   3.875992945789105*^9, 3.875992946508586*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[12]:=",ExpressionUUID->"06fd1343-45f5-4f18-97c9-e5491ce76163"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The arguments of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "DefMetric"],ExpressionUUID->"4b39f0c1-07e4-4731-b110-f61a6213e599"],
 " are the sign of determinant, the metric and the adapted Levi-Civita \
connection. \nThe option ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "SymbolOfCovD"],ExpressionUUID->"89f9fe22-d828-4058-9afb-6d9807629474"],
 " specifies the postfix and prefix forms of the covariant derivative.\n\n",
 StyleBox["In ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData["xAct`"],
  FormatType->StandardForm,
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"9c197d07-1dfd-4b31-8b57-61854950a4cc"],
 StyleBox[" the lower indices are marked by minus sign.",
  FontWeight->"Bold"]
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.874664138245167*^9, 3.874664215169526*^9}, 
   3.874724760194075*^9, {3.87599290501858*^9, 
   3.8759929117143106`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a6483658-48a5-4da7-95f5-\
1f4068c1706e"],

Cell[TextData[{
 Cell[BoxData[
 "PrintAs"],ExpressionUUID->"c3427d3d-d4c0-48ee-9201-cfd18e8f8ee4"],
 " is a common function and option telling ",
 Cell[BoxData["xAct`"],ExpressionUUID->"566036f2-f2de-48e3-9c57-931fe41fdb8c"],
 " how to print related symbols. \nIt's convenient to print the Levi-Civita \
symbol as ",
 Cell[BoxData["\"\<\[Epsilon]\>\""],
  FormatType->StandardForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "db30b970-617f-4b9c-a843-7ca0cead4dfd"],
 ", and the Riemann tensor, Ricci tensor and Ricci scalar all as ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "\"\<R\>\""],ExpressionUUID->"d07676be-5bfb-46e1-842a-2275b4112f08"],
 "."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.874664138245167*^9, 3.874664215169526*^9}, {
  3.875908683522744*^9, 3.875908701248767*^9}, {3.875908738758651*^9, 
  3.8759087438702507`*^9}, {3.8759929352502527`*^9, 3.875992936631572*^9}, {
  3.875995451555427*^9, 
  3.875995480007044*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"de007c75-a3b9-4568-b2ae-\
8dc11a1adc67"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"PrintAs", "[", "RiemannCD", "]"}], "^=", "\"\<R\>\""}], 
  ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"PrintAs", "[", "RicciCD", "]"}], "^=", "\"\<R\>\""}], 
  ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"PrintAs", "[", "RicciScalarCD", "]"}], "^=", "\"\<R\>\""}], 
  ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"PrintAs", "[", "epsilonmetric", "]"}], "^=", 
   "\"\<\[Epsilon]\>\""}], ";"}]}], "Code",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.87599538417264*^9, 3.875995392997744*^9}, {
  3.87599543793311*^9, 3.875995439619279*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[13]:=",ExpressionUUID->"1743f7c9-433c-4995-977e-2582d4e1d5d4"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The tangent bundle ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "TangentM"],ExpressionUUID->"edb1c05a-f04c-4976-b5f3-746013ddda03"],
 " will be automatically defined after ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "DefManifold"],ExpressionUUID->"a9825432-48d0-4349-845a-69bcdd9bf9ca"],
 ".\nSimilarly the metric determinant ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "Detmetric"],ExpressionUUID->"9e6d1f05-21c9-4d15-a3e1-88dac943c735"],
 " and curvature-related tensors will be defined after ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "DefMetric"],ExpressionUUID->"15d9868e-c0cc-4eb8-88ed-5f60a253cda3"],
 ". \n\nThe naming of these objects obeys the following form:\n\t\
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]key word\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]<>\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]name of the parent object\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]"
}], "Text",
